{"title_page": "Amar (2019 film)", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2019}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=March 2019}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = Amar\n| image          = Amar_(2019_film).jpg\n| caption        = \n| film_name      = \n| director       = Nagashekar\n| producer       = Sandesh Nagaraj\n| screenplay     = Nagashekar\n| story          = Nagashekar\n| starring       = Abhishek Gowda <br /> [[Tanya Hope]] <br /> [[Devaraj]] <br /> [[Sudharani]]\n| music          = [[Arjun Janya]]\n| cinematography = [[Satya Hegde]]\n| editing        = [[Srikanth Gowda]]\n| studio         = Sandesh Productions\n| released       = {{Film date|df=yes|2019|05|31}}\n| country        = India\n| language       = Kannada\n| runtime        = \n| budget         = \n| gross          =  \n}}\n\n'''''Amar''''' is a 2019 Indian [[Kannada language|Kannada]] [[romance film|romantic]] [[action film]] directed by Nagashekar and produced by Sandesh Nagaraj under Sandesh Productions banner.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.newindianexpress.com/entertainment/kannada/2018/mar/20/abhisheks-debut-to-be-helmed-by-nagashekar-1790038.html|title=Abhishek\u2019s debut to be helmed by Nagashekar?|publisher=The New Indian Express.com|date=20 March 2018}}</ref> The film stars Abhishek Gowda, son of veteran actor [[Ambarish]],<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.thenewsminute.com/article/shooting-starts-abhishek-s-debut-film-amar-82019|title=Shooting starts for Abhishek's debut film 'Amar'|publisher=The News Minute|date=28 May 2018}}</ref> making his acting debut and [[Tanya Hope]] in the lead roles.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.thenewsminute.com/article/abhishek-ambareesh-and-tanya-hope-play-bikers-amar-83696|title=Abhishek Ambareesh and Tanya Hope play bikers in Amar|publisher= The News Minute|date=26 June 2018}}</ref> The supporting cast includes [[Devaraj]], [[Sudharani]], [[Chikkanna]] and [[Sadhu Kokila]]. Actor [[Darshan (actor)|Darshan]] features in an extended guest role besides [[Anup Bhandari]] and [[Rachita Ram]] in special appearance. <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cinemaexpress.com/stories/news/2019/jan/08/darshan-to-feature-in-abhisheks-debut-film-amar-9552.html|title= Darshan to feature in Abhishek's debut film, Amar|publisher=Cinema Express|date=8 January 2019}}</ref>\n\nThe principal photography began on 28 May 2018 and the filming is set to be held in and around [[Bengaluru]] and [[Switzerland]].<ref name=am>{{cite web|url=http://www.newindianexpress.com/entertainment/kannada/2018/nov/11/abhishek-and-tanya-hope-battle-cold-in-switzerland-for-amar-1896907.html|title=Abhishek and Tanya Hope battle cold in Switzerland for Amar|publisher=The New Indian Express|date=11 November 2018}}</ref> The technical crew members for the film include [[Arjun Janya]] as the music composer, [[Satya Hegde]] as the cinematographer and Deepu S. Kumar as the editor.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.newsbugz.com/amar-kannada-movie/|title=Amar Kannada Movie (2019)|publisher= News Bugs|date=27 September 2018}}</ref>\n\n== Plot ==\nAmarnath (Abhishek), a happy-go-lucky youth, lives with his father (Deepak Shetty) and mother. Amar befriends Bobby then joins her and her team on the Saving Nature mission and eventually falls in love with her.\n\nBobby's father (Devaraj) decides to marry her to a businessman, Darshan's brother (Anup Bhandari). Amar breaks up with her, she leaves him heartbroken. After some years, he finds her and tries to convince her. In the climax, they reunite with the help of Darshan.\n\n== Cast ==\n* Abhishek Gowda as Amar\n* [[Tanya Hope]] as Bobby\n* [[Devaraj]] as Bobby's father\n* [[Sudharani]] as Amar's mother\n* [[Sadhu Kokila]] as Amar's uncle\n* [[Chikkanna]] as Amar's friend\n* [[Deepak Shetty]] as Amar's father\n* [[Darshan (actor)|Darshan]] as Arun Subbiah in a special appearance\n* [[Anup Bhandari]] as Varun Subbiah in a special appearance in \"Joru Paattu\"\n* [[Arjun Janya]] in a special appearance in \"Joru Paattu\"\n* [[Rachita Ram]] in a guest appearance in the song \"Joru Paattu\"\n* [[Arun Sagar]] as Devaraj's aide\n\n== Production ==\nThe film marked the acting debut of Abhishek, son of Ambareesh.<ref>https://www.ibtimes.co.in/ambarishs-son-abhishek-gowda-foray-into-sandalwood-amar-770424</ref> The filming was held in Bengaluru and Switzerland.<ref name=am />\n\n==Soundtrack==\n[[Arjun Janya]] is set to compose the [[Film score|score]] and [[soundtrack]] for the film. Reportedly, the title song of Abhishek's father [[Ambarish]] starrer ''[[Olavina Udugore]]'' (1987) has been recreated in the film.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/kannada/movies/news/ambareeshs-1987-movie-title-song-to-be-re-created-for-son-abhisheks-upcoming-film-amar/articleshow/66864321.cms|title=Ambareesh's 1987 movie title song to be re-created for son Abhishek's upcoming film 'Amar'|publisher=The Times of India|date=29 November 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/kannada/movies/news/first-video-song-of-amar-to-be-out-on-ugadi/articleshow/68703270.cms|title=First video song of Amar to be out on Ugadi - Times of India|website=The Times of India}}</ref> The song \"Marethuhoyithe\" shot in Switzerland was a huge hit and was choreographed by [[B. Dhananjay]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.newindianexpress.com/entertainment/kannada/2018/nov/11/abhishek-and-tanya-hope-battle-cold-in-switzerland-for-amar-1896907.html|title=Abhishek and Tanya Hope battle cold in Switzerland for Amar|website=The New Indian Express}}</ref>\n{{Tracklist\n| extra_column = Singer(s)\n| title1 =  Marethuhiythe\n| extra1 = [[Sanjith Hegde]]\n| lyrics1 =\n| length1 =\n| title2 = Summane Heege Ninnane\n| length2 =\n| lyrics2 =\n| extra2 = [[Shreya Ghoshal]], [[Sonu Nigam]]\n| title3 = Onde Aetige\n| extra3 = Shreya Ghoshal, [[Armaan Malik]]\n| length3 =\n| lyrics3 =\n| title4 = Joru Paattu\n| length4 =\n| lyrics4 =\n| extra4 = [[Jassie Gift]]\n| title5 = Kambani\n| lyrics5 =\n| extra5 = Shreya Ghoshal, Sonu Nigam\n| length5 =\n| title6 =\n| length6 =\n| lyrics6 =\n| extra6 =\n| title7 =\n| extra7 =\n| length7 =\n| lyrics7 =\n| title8 =\n| lyrics8 =\n| length8 =\n| extra8 =\n}}\n\n== Release ==\nThe film was released in 300 theatres across Karnataka. The film received negative reviews from critics and audiences alike and performed average.<ref>https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/kannada/movie-reviews/amar/movie-review/69595548.cms</ref><ref>https://www.thenewsminute.com/article/amar-review-abhishek-gowdas-big-debut-pleasant-love-story-102763</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links ==\n* {{IMDb title|9626774}}\n* [https://www.filmibeat.com/kannada/movies/abhishek-ambareesh-amar.html  Amar Movie (2019)]\n\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Amar}}\n[[Category:Kannada-language films]]\n[[Category:Indian films]]\n[[Category:2010s Kannada-language films]]\n[[Category:Indian action films]]\n[[Category:Indian romance films]]\n[[Category:Films shot in Karnataka]]\n[[Category:Films scored by Arjun Janya]]\n[[Category:Foreign films shot in Switzerland]]\n[[Category:Films featuring an item number]]\n[[Category:Masala films]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2019}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=March 2019}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = Amar\n| image          = Amar_(2019_film).jpg\n| caption        = \n| film_name      = \n| director       = Nagashekar\n| producer       = Sandesh Nagaraj\n| screenplay     = Nagashekar\n| story          = Nagashekar\n| starring       = Abhishek Gowda <br /> [[Tanya Hope]] <br /> [[Devaraj]] <br /> [[Sudharani]]\n| music          = [[Arjun Janya]]\n| cinematography = [[Satya Hegde]]\n| editing        = [[Srikanth Gowda]]\n| studio         = Sandesh Productions\n| released       = {{Film date|df=yes|2019|05|31}}\n| country        = India\n| language       = Kannada\n| runtime        = \n| budget         = \n| gross          =  \n}}\n\n'''''Amar''''' is a 2019 Indian [[Kannada language|Kannada]] [[romance film|romantic]] [[action film]] directed by Nagashekar and produced by Sandesh Nagaraj under Sandesh Productions banner.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.newindianexpress.com/entertainment/kannada/2018/mar/20/abhisheks-debut-to-be-helmed-by-nagashekar-1790038.html|title=Abhishek\u2019s debut to be helmed by Nagashekar?|publisher=The New Indian Express.com|date=20 March 2018}}</ref> The film stars Abhishek Gowda, son of veteran actor [[Ambarish]],<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.thenewsminute.com/article/shooting-starts-abhishek-s-debut-film-amar-82019|title=Shooting starts for Abhishek's debut film 'Amar'|publisher=The News Minute|date=28 May 2018}}</ref> making his acting debut and [[Tanya Hope]] in the lead roles.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.thenewsminute.com/article/abhishek-ambareesh-and-tanya-hope-play-bikers-amar-83696|title=Abhishek Ambareesh and Tanya Hope play bikers in Amar|publisher= The News Minute|date=26 June 2018}}</ref> The supporting cast includes [[Devaraj]], [[Sudharani]], [[Chikkanna]] and [[Sadhu Kokila]]. Actor [[Darshan (actor)|Darshan]] features in an extended guest role besides [[Anup Bhandari]] and [[Rachita Ram]] in special appearance. <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cinemaexpress.com/stories/news/2019/jan/08/darshan-to-feature-in-abhisheks-debut-film-amar-9552.html|title= Darshan to feature in Abhishek's debut film, Amar|publisher=Cinema Express|date=8 January 2019}}</ref>\n\nThe principal photography began on 28 May 2018 and the filming is set to be held in and around [[Bengaluru]] and [[Switzerland]].<ref name=am>{{cite web|url=http://www.newindianexpress.com/entertainment/kannada/2018/nov/11/abhishek-and-tanya-hope-battle-cold-in-switzerland-for-amar-1896907.html|title=Abhishek and Tanya Hope battle cold in Switzerland for Amar|publisher=The New Indian Express|date=11 November 2018}}</ref> The technical crew members for the film include [[Arjun Janya]] as the music composer, [[Satya Hegde]] as the cinematographer and Deepu S. Kumar as the editor.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.newsbugz.com/amar-kannada-movie/|title=Amar Kannada Movie (2019)|publisher= News Bugs|date=27 September 2018}}</ref>\n\n== Plot ==\nAmarnath (Abhishek), a happy-go-lucky youth, lives with his father (Deepak Shetty) and mother. Amar befriends Bobby then joins her and her team on the Saving Nature mission and eventually falls in love with her.\n\nBobby's father (Devaraj) decides to marry her to a businessman, Darshan's brother (Anup Bhandari). Amar breaks up with her, she leaves him heartbroken. After some years, he finds her and tries to convince her. In the climax, they reunite with the help of Darshan.\n\n== Cast ==\n* Abhishek Gowda as Amar\n* [[Tanya Hope]] as Bobby\n* [[Devaraj]] as Bobby's father\n* [[Sudharani]] as Amar's mother\n* [[Sadhu Kokila]] as Amar's uncle\n* [[Chikkanna]] as Amar's friend\n* [[Deepak Shetty]] As Amar's father\n* [[Darshan (actor)|Darshan]] as Arun Subbiah in a special appearance\n* [[Anup Bhandari]] as Varun Subbiah in a special appearance in \"Joru Paattu\"\n* [[Arjun Janya]] in a special appearance in \"Joru Paattu\"\n* [[Rachita Ram]] as Guest appearance in song \"Joru paattu\"\n* [[Arun Sagar]] as Devaraj's aide\n\n== Production ==\nThe film marked the acting debut of Abhishek, son of Ambareesh.<ref>https://www.ibtimes.co.in/ambarishs-son-abhishek-gowda-foray-into-sandalwood-amar-770424</ref> The filming was held in Bengaluru and Switzerland.<ref name=am />\n\n==Soundtrack==\n[[Arjun Janya]] is set to compose the [[Film score|score]] and [[soundtrack]] for the film. Reportedly, the title song of Abhishek's father [[Ambarish]] starrer ''[[Olavina Udugore]]'' (1987) has been recreated in the film.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/kannada/movies/news/ambareeshs-1987-movie-title-song-to-be-re-created-for-son-abhisheks-upcoming-film-amar/articleshow/66864321.cms|title=Ambareesh's 1987 movie title song to be re-created for son Abhishek's upcoming film 'Amar'|publisher=The Times of India|date=29 November 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/kannada/movies/news/first-video-song-of-amar-to-be-out-on-ugadi/articleshow/68703270.cms|title=First video song of Amar to be out on Ugadi - Times of India|website=The Times of India}}</ref> The song \"Marethuhoyithe\" shot in Switzerland was a huge hit and was choreographed by [[B. Dhananjay]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.newindianexpress.com/entertainment/kannada/2018/nov/11/abhishek-and-tanya-hope-battle-cold-in-switzerland-for-amar-1896907.html|title=Abhishek and Tanya Hope battle cold in Switzerland for Amar|website=The New Indian Express}}</ref>\n{{Tracklist\n| extra_column = Singer(s)\n| title1 =  Marethuhiythe\n| extra1 = [[Sanjith Hegde]]\n| lyrics1 =\n| length1 =\n| title2 = Summane Heege Ninnane\n| length2 =\n| lyrics2 =\n| extra2 = [[Shreya Ghoshal]], [[Sonu Nigam]]\n| title3 = Onde Aetige\n| extra3 = Shreya Ghoshal, [[Armaan Malik]]\n| length3 =\n| lyrics3 =\n| title4 = Joru Paattu\n| length4 =\n| lyrics4 =\n| extra4 = [[Jassie Gift]]\n| title5 = Kambani\n| lyrics5 =\n| extra5 = Shreya Ghoshal, Sonu Nigam\n| length5 =\n| title6 =\n| length6 =\n| lyrics6 =\n| extra6 =\n| title7 =\n| extra7 =\n| length7 =\n| lyrics7 =\n| title8 =\n| lyrics8 =\n| length8 =\n| extra8 =\n}}\n\n== Release ==\nThe film was released in 300 theatres across Karnataka. The film received negative reviews from critics and audiences alike and performed average.<ref>https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/kannada/movie-reviews/amar/movie-review/69595548.cms</ref><ref>https://www.thenewsminute.com/article/amar-review-abhishek-gowdas-big-debut-pleasant-love-story-102763</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links ==\n* {{IMDb title|9626774}}\n* [https://www.filmibeat.com/kannada/movies/abhishek-ambareesh-amar.html  Amar Movie (2019)]\n\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Amar}}\n[[Category:Kannada-language films]]\n[[Category:Indian films]]\n