ddelan]]   \n| date = 1922\n| show_artist= yes\n| artist = \n| type = Column and sphere \n| material = Stone \n| dimensions = \n| designation = \n| coordinates=\n| show_wikidata= yes\n| wikidata = \n| notes = <ref>{{cite web |author=|url= https://historypoints.org/index.php?page=dolwyddelan-war-memorial|title= Dolwyddelan war memorial |date=|accessdate= 16 March 2020|work=historypoints.org}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |author=|url=https://www.iwm.org.uk/memorials/item/memorial/17366 |title=War Memorials Register: Dolwyddelan |date= |accessdate=14 March 2020|work= Imperial War Museum}}</ref>\n}}\n{{Public art footer}}\n\n==Llandudno==\n{{Public art header|show_architect=no|show_material=yes|show_dimensions=yes|show_owner=no|show_wikidata=yes}}\n{{Public art row\n| image = Queen Victoria in the Happy Valley. - geograph.org.uk - 341460.jpg \n| commonscat = \n| subject = [[Queen Victoria]]\n| location = Happy Valley, Great Orme, [[Llandudno]]  \n| date = 1887\n| show_artist= yes\n| artist = \n| type = Fountain and canopy \n| material = Stone \n| dimensions = \n| designation = Grade II\n| coordinates=\n| show_wikidata= yes\n| wikidata = Q29485153\n| notes = <ref>{{cadw|num=5800|desc= Jubilee Fountain & Monument to Queen Victoria, Llandudno|accessdate=16 March 2020}}</ref>\n}}\n{{Public art row\n| image = Llandudno War Memorial - geograph.org.uk - 1719803.jpg\n| commonscat = Llandudno War Memorial\n| subject = War Memorial \n| location = South Parade, [[Llandudno]]\n| date = 1922\n| show_artist= yes\n| artist = S. Colwyn Foulkes\n| type = Obelisk \n| material = Granite\n| dimensions = 15.2m high\n| designation = Grade II\n| coordinates=\n| show_wikidata= yes\n| wikidata = Q29483324\n| notes = <ref>{{cadw|num= 3475|desc= Llandudno war memorial|accessdate=14 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |author=|url= https://historypoints.org/index.php?page=llandudno-war-memorial|title= Llandudno war memorial |date=|accessdate= 14 March 2020|work=historypoints.org}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |aut